    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Hi @Haroenv \n\nWe're seeing the same high-severity vulnerability reported by `yarn audit --groups dependencies`. Because this package is deployed to production, our security team has opened an alert. Will there be a react-instantsearch release that updates `preact to ^10.28.2`? If not, could you suggest any short-term mitigations we can apply until a release is available?\n\nFor reference, we're using `react-instantsearch@7.22.1`.\n\n\nThank you,\nArindam",
